def: An instrument for measuring the size of skulls.
Like a pill; small; insignificant. [R.] G. Eliot.
Auxiliary. [Archaic]The auxiliar troops and Trojan hosts appear. Pope.
Of, pertaining to, or derived from, pentadecane, or designatingan acid related to it.
To beg; to pilfer; to skelder. [Prov. Eng.& Scot.] Sir W.Scott.
To mar the figure of; to render less complete, perfect, orbeautiful in appearance; to deface; to deform.Disfiguring not God's likeness, but their own. Milton.
1. (Zo√∂l.) An amphibious animal of the genus Rana and relatedgenera, of many species. Frogs swim rapidly, and take long leaps onland. Many of the species utter loud notes in the springtime.
